  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Micah of Moresheth
        during the years when Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah were kings of Judah. The
        visions he saw concerned both Samaria and Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Grief over Samaria and Jerusalem
      content: "Attention! Let all the people of the world listen!\n\tLet the earth
        and everything in it hear.\n\tThe Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is
        making accusations against you;\n\tthe Lord speaks from his holy Temple.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming!\n\tHe leaves his
        throne in heaven\n\tand tramples the heights of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The mountains melt beneath his feet\n\tand flow into the valleys\n\tlike
        wax in a fire,\n\tlike water pouring down a hill.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And why is this happening?\n\tBecause of the rebellion of Israel[COMMENT[0]]\u2014\n\tyes,
        the sins of the whole nation.\n\tWho is to blame for Israel\u2019s rebellion?\n\tSamaria,
        its capital city!\n\tWhere is the center of idolatry in Judah?\n\tIn Jerusalem,
        its capital!  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jacob; '
        - ft: "also in 1:5b. The names \u201CJacob\u201D and \u201CIsrael\u201D are
            often interchanged throughout the Old Testament, referring sometimes
            to the individual patriarch and sometimes to the nation."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, will make the city
        of Samaria\n\ta heap of ruins.\n\tHer streets will be plowed up\n\tfor planting
        vineyards.\n\tI will roll the stones of her walls into the valley below,\n\texposing
        her foundations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All her carved images will be smashed.\n\tAll her sacred treasures
        will be burned.\n\tThese things were bought with the money\n\tearned by her
        prostitution,\n\tand they will now be carried away\n\tto pay prostitutes
        elsewhere.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, I will mourn and lament.\n\tI will walk around barefoot
        and naked.\n\tI will howl like a jackal\n\tand moan like an owl.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For my people\u2019s wound\n\tis too deep to heal.\n\tIt has reached
        into Judah,\n\teven to the gates of Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t tell our enemies in Gath[COMMENT[0]];\n\tdon\u2019t weep
        at all.\n\tYou people in Beth-leaphrah,[COMMENT[1]]roll in the dust to show
        your despair.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:10a '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Gath '
        - ft: "sounds like the Hebrew term for \u201Ctell.\u201D"
          body: 
      - number: '1:10b '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Beth-leaphrah '
        - ft: "means \u201Chouse of dust.\u201D"
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "You people in Shaphir,[COMMENT[0]]go as captives into exile\u2014naked
        and ashamed.\n\tThe people of Zaanan[COMMENT[1]]dare not come outside their
        walls.\n\tThe people of Beth-ezel[COMMENT[2]] mourn,\n\tfor their house has
        no support.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:11a '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Shaphir '
        - ft: "means \u201Cpleasant.\u201D"
          body: 
      - number: '1:11b '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Zaanan '
        - ft: "sounds like the Hebrew term for \u201Ccome out.\u201D"
          body: 
      - number: '1:11c '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Beth-ezel '
        - ft: "means \u201Cadjoining house.\u201D"
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Maroth[COMMENT[0]] anxiously wait for relief,\n\tbut
        only bitterness awaits them\n\tas the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        judgment reaches\n\teven to the gates of Jerusalem.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Maroth '
        - ft: "sounds like the Hebrew term for \u201Cbitter.\u201D"
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Harness your chariot horses and flee,\n\tyou people of Lachish.[COMMENT[0]]You
        were the first city in Judah\n\tto follow Israel in her rebellion,\n\tand
        you led Jerusalem[COMMENT[1]] into sin.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:13a '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Lachish '
        - ft: "sounds like the Hebrew term for \u201Cteam of horses.\u201D"
          body: 
      - number: '1:13b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the daughter of Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "Send farewell gifts to Moresheth-gath[COMMENT[0]];\n\tthere is no
        hope of saving it.\n\tThe town of Aczib[COMMENT[1]]has deceived the kings
        of Israel.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:14a '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Moresheth '
        - ft: "sounds like the Hebrew term for \u201Cgift\u201D or \u201Cdowry.\u201D"
          body: 
      - number: '1:14b '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Aczib '
        - ft: "means \u201Cdeception.\u201D"
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "O people of Mareshah,[COMMENT[0]]I will bring a conqueror to capture
        your town.\n\tAnd the leaders[COMMENT[1]] of Israel\n\twill go to Adullam.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:15a '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Mareshah '
        - ft: "sounds like the Hebrew term for \u201Cconqueror.\u201D"
          body: 
      - number: '1:15b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the glory.
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, people of Judah, shave your heads in sorrow,\n\tfor the children
        you love will be snatched away.\n\tMake yourselves as bald as a vulture,\n\tfor
        your little ones will be exiled to distant lands."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Judgment against Wealthy Oppressors
      content: "What sorrow awaits you who lie awake at night,\n\tthinking up evil
        plans.\n\tYou rise at dawn and hurry to carry them out,\n\tsimply because
        you have the power to do so.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you want a piece of land,\n\tyou find a way to seize it.\n\tWhen
        you want someone\u2019s house,\n\tyou take it by fraud and violence.\n\tYou
        cheat a man of his property,\n\tstealing his family\u2019s inheritance.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CI
        will reward your evil with evil;\n\tyou won\u2019t be able to pull your neck
        out of the noose.\n\tYou will no longer walk around proudly,\n\tfor it will
        be a terrible time.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day your enemies will make fun of you\n\tby singing this
        song of despair about you:\n\t\u201CWe are finished,\n\tcompletely ruined!\n\tGod
        has confiscated our land,\n\ttaking it from us.\n\tHe has given our fields\n\tto
        those who betrayed us.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: to those who took us captive.
    - title: 
      content: "Others will set your boundaries then,\n\tand the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        people will have no say\n\tin how the land is divided.  "
      comments: []
    - title: True and False Prophets
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t say such things,\u201D\n\tthe people respond.[COMMENT[0]]\u201CDon\u2019t
        prophesy like that.\n\tSuch disasters will never come our way!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'the prophets respond; '
        - ft: 'Hebrew reads '
          body: they prophesy.
    - title: 
      content: "Should you talk that way, O family of Israel?[COMMENT[0]]Will the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Spirit have patience with such behavior?\n\tIf
        you would do what is right,\n\tyou would find my words comforting.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'O house of Jacob? '
        - ft: See note on 1:5a.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Yet to this very hour\n\tmy people rise against me like an enemy!\n\tYou
        steal the shirts right off the backs\n\tof those who trusted you,\n\tmaking
        them as ragged as men\n\treturning from battle.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have evicted women from their pleasant homes\n\tand forever stripped
        their children of all that God would give them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Up! Begone!\n\tThis is no longer your land and home,\n\tfor you have
        filled it with sin\n\tand ruined it completely.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Suppose a prophet full of lies would say to you,\n\t\u201CI\u2019ll
        preach to you the joys of wine and alcohol!\u201D\n\tThat\u2019s just the
        kind of prophet you would like!  "
      comments: []
    - title: Hope for Restoration
      content: "\u201CSomeday, O Israel, I will gather you;\n\tI will gather the
        remnant who are left.\n\tI will bring you together again like sheep in a
        pen,\n\tlike a flock in its pasture.\n\tYes, your land will again\n\tbe filled
        with noisy crowds!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your leader will break out\n\tand lead you out of exile,\n\tout through
        the gates of the enemy cities,\n\tback to your own land.\n\tYour king will
        lead you;\n\tthe <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>\n\thimself will guide you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Judgment against Israel\u2019s Leaders"
      content: "I said, \u201CListen, you leaders of Israel!\n\tYou are supposed
        to know right from wrong,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but you are the very ones\n\twho hate good and love evil.\n\tYou
        skin my people alive\n\tand tear the flesh from their bones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, you eat my people\u2019s flesh,\n\tstrip off their skin,\n\tand
        break their bones.\n\tYou chop them up\n\tlike meat for the cooking pot.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you beg the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for help in times of
        trouble!\n\tDo you really expect him to answer?\n\tAfter all the evil you
        have done,\n\the won\u2019t even look at you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CYou false
        prophets are leading my people astray!\n\tYou promise peace for those who
        give you food,\n\tbut you declare war on those who refuse to feed you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now the night will close around you,\n\tcutting off all your visions.\n\tDarkness
        will cover you,\n\tputting an end to your predictions.\n\tThe sun will set
        for you prophets,\n\tand your day will come to an end.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you seers will be put to shame,\n\tand you fortune-tellers will
        be disgraced.\n\tAnd you will cover your faces\n\tbecause there is no answer
        from God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But as for me, I am filled with power\u2014\n\twith the Spirit of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tI am filled with justice and strength\n\tto
        boldly declare Israel\u2019s sin and rebellion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to me, you leaders of Israel!\n\tYou hate justice and twist
        all that is right.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You are building Jerusalem\n\ton a foundation of murder and corruption.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You rulers make decisions based on bribes;\n\tyou priests teach God\u2019s
        laws only for a price;\n\tyou prophets won\u2019t prophesy unless you are
        paid.\n\tYet all of you claim to depend on the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CNo
        harm can come to us,\u201D you say,\n\t\u201Cfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is here among us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Because of you, Mount Zion will be plowed like an open field;\n\tJerusalem
        will be reduced to ruins!\n\tA thicket will grow on the heights\n\twhere
        the Temple now stands."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Future Reign"
      content: "In the last days, the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        house\n\twill be the highest of all\u2014\n\tthe most important place on
        earth.\n\tIt will be raised above the other hills,\n\tand people from all
        over the world will stream there to worship.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People from many nations will come and say,\n\t\u201CCome, let us
        go up to the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tto the house
        of Jacob\u2019s God.\n\tThere he will teach us his ways,\n\tand we will walk
        in his paths.\u201D\n\tFor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s teaching
        will go out from Zion;\n\this word will go out from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will mediate between peoples\n\tand
        will settle disputes between strong nations far away.\n\tThey will hammer
        their swords into plowshares\n\tand their spears into pruning hooks.\n\tNation
        will no longer fight against nation,\n\tnor train for war anymore.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Everyone will live in peace and prosperity,\n\tenjoying their own
        grapevines and fig trees,\n\tfor there will be nothing to fear.\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies\n\thas made this promise!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though the nations around us follow their idols,\n\twe will follow
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God forever and ever.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Return from Exile"
      content: "\u201CIn that coming day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201CI
        will gather together those who are lame,\n\tthose who have been exiles,\n\tand
        those whom I have filled with grief.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who are weak will survive as a remnant;\n\tthose who were exiles
        will become a strong nation.\n\tThen I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        will rule from Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]]as their king forever.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Mount Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "As for you, Jerusalem,\n\tthe citadel of God\u2019s people,[COMMENT[0]]your
        royal might and power\n\twill come back to you again.\n\tThe kingship will
        be restored\n\tto my precious Jerusalem.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: As for you, Migdal-eder, / the Ophel of the daughter of Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "But why are you now screaming in terror?\n\tHave you no king to lead
        you?\n\tHave your wise people all died?\n\tPain has gripped you like a woman
        in childbirth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Writhe and groan like a woman in labor,\n\tyou people of Jerusalem,[COMMENT[0]]for
        now you must leave this city\n\tto live in the open country.\n\tYou will
        soon be sent in exile\n\tto distant Babylon.\n\tBut the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will rescue you there;\n\the will redeem you from the grip of your enemies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: O daughter of Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "Now many nations have gathered against you.\n\t\u201CLet her be desecrated,\u201D
        they say.\n\t\u201CLet us see the destruction of Jerusalem.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: of Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "But they do not know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s thoughts\n\tor
        understand his plan.\n\tThese nations don\u2019t know\n\tthat he is gathering
        them together\n\tto be beaten and trampled\n\tlike sheaves of grain on a
        threshing floor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRise up and crush the nations, O Jerusalem!\u201D[COMMENT[0]]says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CFor I will give you iron horns
        and bronze hooves,\n\tso you can trample many nations to pieces.\n\tYou will
        present their stolen riches to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\ttheir
        wealth to the Lord of all the earth.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "\u201CRise up and thresh, O daughter of Zion.\u201D"
