    - title: A Ruler from Bethlehem
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]But you, O Bethlehem Ephrathah,\n\tare only a small
        village among all the people of Judah.\n\tYet a ruler of Israel,\n\twhose
        origins are in the distant past,\n\twill come from you on my behalf.  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '5:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 5:2-15 are numbered 5:1-14 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Israel will be abandoned to their enemies\n\tuntil
        the woman in labor gives birth.\n\tThen at last his fellow countrymen\n\twill
        return from exile to their own land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he will stand to lead his flock with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        strength,\n\tin the majesty of the name of the <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>\n\this
        God.\n\tThen his people will live there undisturbed,\n\tfor he will be highly
        honored around the world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he will be the source of peace.\n\tWhen the Assyrians invade
        our land\n\tand break through our defenses,\n\twe will appoint seven rulers
        to watch over us,\n\teight princes to lead us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will rule Assyria with drawn swords\n\tand enter the gates of
        the land of Nimrod.\n\tHe will rescue us from the Assyrians\n\twhen they
        pour over the borders to invade our land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Remnant Purified
      content: "Then the remnant left in Israel[COMMENT[0]]will take their place
        among the nations.\n\tThey will be like dew sent by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tor
        like rain falling on the grass,\n\twhich no one can hold back\n\tand no one
        can restrain.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'in Jacob; '
        - ft: also in 5:8. See note on 1:5a.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The remnant left in Israel\n\twill take their place among the nations.\n\tThey
        will be like a lion among the animals of the forest,\n\tlike a strong young
        lion among flocks of sheep and goats,\n\tpouncing and tearing as they go\n\twith
        no rescuer in sight.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Israel will stand up to their foes,\n\tand all their
        enemies will be wiped out.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201CI
        will slaughter your horses\n\tand destroy your chariots.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will tear down your walls\n\tand demolish your defenses.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will put an end to all witchcraft,\n\tand there will be no more
        fortune-tellers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will destroy all your idols and sacred pillars,\n\tso you will
        never again worship the work of your own hands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will abolish your idol shrines with their Asherah poles\n\tand
        destroy your pagan cities.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will pour out my vengeance\n\ton all the nations that refuse to
        obey me.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Case against Israel"
      content: "Listen to what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is saying:\n\t\u201CStand
        up and state your case against me.\n\tLet the mountains and hills be called
        to witness your complaints.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And now, O mountains,\n\tlisten to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        complaint!\n\tHe has a case against his people.\n\tHe will bring charges
        against Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO my people, what have I done to you?\n\tWhat have I done to
        make you tired of me?\n\tAnswer me!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I brought you out of Egypt\n\tand redeemed you from slavery.\n\tI
        sent Moses, Aaron, and Miriam to help you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t you remember, my people,\n\thow King Balak of Moab tried
        to have you cursed\n\tand how Balaam son of Beor blessed you instead?\n\tAnd
        remember your journey from Acacia Grove[COMMENT[0]] to Gilgal,\n\twhen I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, did everything I could\n\tto teach you
        about my faithfulness.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Shittim.
    - title: 
      content: "What can we bring to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?\n\tShould
        we bring him burnt offerings?\n\tShould we bow before God Most High\n\twith
        offerings of yearling calves?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Should we offer him thousands of rams\n\tand ten thousand rivers
        of olive oil?\n\tShould we sacrifice our firstborn children\n\tto pay for
        our sins?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, O people, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has told you what is
        good,\n\tand this is what he requires of you:\n\tto do what is right, to
        love mercy,\n\tand to walk humbly with your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Guilt and Punishment"
      content: "Fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> if you are wise!\n\tHis voice
        calls to everyone in Jerusalem:\n\t\u201CThe armies of destruction are coming;\n\tthe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is sending them.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "\u201CListen to the rod. / Who appointed it?\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: "What shall I say about the homes of the wicked\n\tfilled with treasures
        gained by cheating?\n\tWhat about the disgusting practice\n\tof measuring
        out grain with dishonest measures?[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'of using the short ephah? '
        - ft: The ephah was a unit for measuring grain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "How can I tolerate your merchants\n\twho use dishonest scales and
        weights?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The rich among you have become wealthy\n\tthrough extortion and violence.\n\tYour
        citizens are so used to lying\n\tthat their tongues can no longer tell the
        truth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, I will wound you!\n\tI will bring you to ruin for
        all your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will eat but never have enough.\n\tYour hunger pangs and emptiness
        will remain.\n\tAnd though you try to save your money,\n\tit will come to
        nothing in the end.\n\tYou will save a little,\n\tbut I will give it to those
        who conquer you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will plant crops\n\tbut not harvest them.\n\tYou will press your
        olives\n\tbut not get enough oil to anoint yourselves.\n\tYou will trample
        the grapes\n\tbut get no juice to make your wine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You keep only the laws of evil King Omri;\n\tyou follow only the
        example of wicked King Ahab!\n\tTherefore, I will make an example of you,\n\tbringing
        you to complete ruin.\n\tYou will be treated with contempt,\n\tmocked by
        all who see you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Misery Turned to Hope
      content: "How miserable I am!\n\tI feel like the fruit picker after the harvest\n\twho
        can find nothing to eat.\n\tNot a cluster of grapes or a single early fig\n\tcan
        be found to satisfy my hunger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godly people have all disappeared;\n\tnot one honest person is
        left on the earth.\n\tThey are all murderers,\n\tsetting traps even for their
        own brothers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Both their hands are equally skilled at doing evil!\n\tOfficials
        and judges alike demand bribes.\n\tThe people with influence get what they
        want,\n\tand together they scheme to twist justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even the best of them is like a brier;\n\tthe most honest is as dangerous
        as a hedge of thorns.\n\tBut your judgment day is coming swiftly now.\n\tYour
        time of punishment is here, a time of confusion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t trust anyone\u2014\n\tnot your best friend or even your
        wife!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the son despises his father.\n\tThe daughter defies her mother.\n\tThe
        daughter-in-law defies her mother-in-law.\n\tYour enemies are right in your
        own household!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As for me, I look to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for help.\n\tI
        wait confidently for God to save me,\n\tand my God will certainly hear me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not gloat over me, my enemies!\n\tFor though I fall, I will rise
        again.\n\tThough I sit in darkness,\n\tthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        be my light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will be patient as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> punishes me,\n\tfor
        I have sinned against him.\n\tBut after that, he will take up my case\n\tand
        give me justice for all I have suffered from my enemies.\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will bring me into the light,\n\tand I will see his righteousness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then my enemies will see that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is
        on my side.\n\tThey will be ashamed that they taunted me, saying,\n\t\u201CSo
        where is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2014\n\tthat God of yours?\u201D\n\tWith
        my own eyes I will see their downfall;\n\tthey will be trampled like mud
        in the streets.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day, Israel, your cities will be rebuilt,\n\tand your borders
        will be extended.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People from many lands will come and honor you\u2014\n\tfrom Assyria
        all the way to the towns of Egypt,\n\tfrom Egypt all the way to the Euphrates
        River,[COMMENT[0]]and from distant seas and mountains.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the river.
    - title: 
      content: "But the land[COMMENT[0]] will become empty and desolate\n\tbecause
        of the wickedness of those who live there.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: earth.
    - title: "\u2019s Compassion on Israel"
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, protect your people with your
        shepherd\u2019s staff;\n\tlead your flock, your special possession.\n\tThough
        they live alone in a thicket\n\ton the heights of Mount Carmel,[COMMENT[0]]let
        them graze in the fertile pastures of Bashan and Gilead\n\tas they did long
        ago.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: surrounded by a fruitful land.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYes,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201CI
        will do mighty miracles for you,\n\tlike those I did when I rescued you\n\tfrom
        slavery in Egypt.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the nations of the world will stand amazed\n\tat what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will do for you.\n\tThey will be embarrassed\n\tat their feeble power.\n\tThey
        will cover their mouths in silent awe,\n\tdeaf to everything around them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Like snakes crawling from their holes,\n\tthey will come out to meet
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.\n\tThey will fear him greatly,\n\ttrembling
        in terror at his presence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where is another God like you,\n\twho pardons the guilt of the remnant,\n\toverlooking
        the sins of his special people?\n\tYou will not stay angry with your people
        forever,\n\tbecause you delight in showing unfailing love.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Once again you will have compassion on us.\n\tYou will trample our
        sins under your feet\n\tand throw them into the depths of the ocean!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will show us your faithfulness and unfailing love\n\tas you promised
        to our ancestors Abraham and Jacob long ago."
      comments: []
